OL,3,CShoplifting on the rise as Welsh
OL,4,Cbusinesses left to foot the bill
OL,6,FExpressing his anger, Mr Kendrick
OL,7,Fsaid: "It infuriates me both the fact
OL,8,Fthey are able to get away with it and
OL,9,Falso that they are back on the streets
OL,10,Fso soon afterwards. This particular
OL,11,Findividual, no more than a few months
OL,12,Fafter the police eventually caught up
OL,13,Fwith him was back shouting abuse at
OL,14,Four staff through the doors. Why can't
OL,15,Fsomething more permanent be done."
OL,17,FSpeaking on behalf of the Federation
OL,18,Fof Small Businesses, Ben Cottam, Head
OL,19,Fof Wales, called for more to be done
OL,20,Fto prioritise the safety of business
OL,21,Fowners facing the risk of shoplifting.
